{
  "texts": [
    "Formative feedback, which transpires during the learning process (Narciss, 2008), is instrumental in enhancing learners' understanding and refining their skills by stimulating learners' metacognitive processes such as selfimprovement and self-monitoring (Butler & Winne, 1995).",
    "This feedback helps learners identify their strengths and weaknesses and target areas they need work on.",
    "It plays an important role in the learning process as it provides students with insights into their areas of proficiency and where additional effort is required (Butler & Winne, 1995).",
    "Kluger and colleagues highlight that formative feedback needs to be specifically related to the task or the learning process to be truly effective (Kluger & DeNisi, 1996).",
    "This involves providing information about the current level of performance or understanding, as well as guidance on how to close the gap between the present understanding and the targeted level of comprehension (Candel et al., 2020)."
  ]
}